# Project Structure Guide

This is a Next.js 14+ project with TypeScript. The main structure follows Next.js App Router conventions:

- [src/app/layout.tsx](mdc:src/app/layout.tsx) is the root layout component
- [src/app/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/page.tsx) is the main page component
- [src/app/globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css) contains global styles
- [next.config.ts](mdc:next.config.ts) contains Next.js configuration
- [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) contains TypeScript configuration

## Key Conventions
- Use the App Router pattern (not pages directory)
- Keep components in `src/components`
- Place page-specific components in their respective page directories
- Store utility functions in `src/utils`
- Place API routes in `src/app/api`